[[cdo:9 nguŏk 2 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[zh-min-nan:9 goe̍h 2 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[zh-yue:九月初二]] {{Lunisolar September}} '''September 2''' is the 2nd day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September|12=draft}} the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Reiki|ja|霊亀|12=draft}} 1st year（{{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[715]] {{ill|October 2|ja|10月2日}}） – By the offering of the Ruikimei, the era name was changed from {{ill|Wadō|ja|和銅|12=draft}} to Reiki. * {{ill|Kennin|ja|建仁|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[1203]] {{ill|October 7|ja|10月7日}}) – The incident known as [[比企能員の変]] occurred: the relative of Minamoto no Yoriie, {{ill|Hiki Nōin|ja|比企能員}}, led a plot to overthrow {{ill|Hojo Tokimasa|ja|北条時政}}; the plan was uncovered and he was executed. * {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1863]] {{ill|October 14|ja|10月14日}}) – The Idogaya Incident occurred. * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1871]] {{ill|October 14|ja|10月14日}}) – The government reformed official salaries, shifting from an annual salary system to a monthly wage system.
== Births == * {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永|12=draft}} 18th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1641]] {{ill|October 5|ja|10月5日}}) – {{ill|Kira Yoshihisa|ja|吉良義央}}, a high-ranking retainer of the Tokugawa shogunate (died [[1702]]). * [[Kansei]] 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1791]] {{ill|September 29|ja|9月29日}}) – {{ill|Sanada Yukinori|ja|真田幸貫}}, the 8th lord of the Matsushiro Domain (died [[1852]]). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1828]] {{ill|October 10|ja|10月10日}}) – {{ill|Matsudaira Harugaku|ja|松平春嶽}}, lord of the late Edo-era Echizen Domain and head of the governmental council (died [[1890]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1841]] {{ill|October 16|ja|10月16日}}) – {{ill|Itō Hirobumi|ja|伊藤博文}}, a prominent statesman and several-time Prime Minister of Japan (died [[1909]]). * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1871]] {{ill|October 15|ja|10月15日}}) – {{ill|Takano Iwazaburō|ja|高野岩三郎}}, a social statistician and social activist (died [[1949]]).
== Deaths == * [[Kaika Tennō]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[158 BC]] {{ill|October 14|ja|10月14日}}) – [[Kōgen Tennō]], the 8th Emperor of Japan. * [[Karoku]] 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[1227]] {{ill|October 13|ja|10月13日}}) – {{ill|Horikawa Tōru|ja|堀川通具}}, a waka poet (born [[1171]]).
