== Events == * [[:en:Reiki (era)|Reiki]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[715]] [[:en:October 2|October 2]]) – Following the presentation of the "Suikime" (瑞亀献上), the era name was changed from [[:en:Wadō (era)|Wadō]] to [[:en:Reiki (era)|Reiki]]. * [[:en:Kennin|Kennin]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1203]] [[:en:October 7|October 7]]) – In the incident known as the "Hikii Nōin no Hen" (比企能員の変), the anti-shogunate plot led by the relative of [[Minamoto no Yoriie]] (外戚・比企能員) against [[:en:Hōjō Tokimasa|Hojo Tokimasa]] was uncovered, and the conspirators were executed. * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1863]] [[:en:October 14|October 14]]) – The "Idogataya Incident" (井土ヶ谷事件) occurred. * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1871]] [[:en:October 14|October 14]]) – The government reformed official salaries, switching from an annual salary system to a monthly payment system.
== Births == * [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] 18th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1641]] [[:en:October 5|October 5]]) – [[:en:Kira Yoshinaka|Kira Yoshihisa]], lord of the Tokugawa high family (died [[1702]]). * [[Kansei]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1791]] [[:en:September 29|September 29]]) – {{ill|Sanada Yukinori|ja|真田幸貫|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sanada Yukinori|qq=}}, the 8th lord of the Matsushiro Domain (died [[1852]]). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 11th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1828]] [[:en:October 10|October 10]]) – [[:en:Matsudaira Yoshinaga|Matsudaira Harugaku]], lord of the late Edo-period Echizen Domain and a government minister (died [[1890]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 12nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1841]] [[:en:October 16|October 16]]) – [[:en:Itō Hirobumi|Itō Hirobumi]], a statesman who served as Prime Minister of Japan in the 1st, 5th, 7th, and 10th administrations (died [[1909]]). * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1871]] [[:en:October 15|October 15]]) – [[:en:Takano Iwasaburo|Kōya Iwasaburō]], a social statistician and social activist (died [[1949]]).
== Deaths == * [[Emperor Kaika]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[158 BC]] [[:en:October 14|October 14]]) – [[:en:Emperor Kōgen|Emperor Kōgen]], the 8th Emperor of Japan. * [[Karoku]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1227]] [[:en:October 13|October 13]]) – {{ill|Horikawa Tōkugu|ja|堀川通具|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Horikawa Tōkugu|qq=}}, a waka poet (born [[1171]]). == Commemorations == {{Empty section|date=2021|qq=}}
