{{Not to be confused with|September 2|qq=September 2}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=九月初二|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 9월 2일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar September|qq=}} '''September 2''' is the 2nd day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September (Nagatsuki)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/September (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Butsumetsu|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Reiki (era)|Reiki]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[715]] [[:en:October 2|October 2]]) – Following the presentation of the "Suikime" (瑞亀献上), the era name was changed from [[:en:Wadō (era)|Wadō]] to [[:en:Reiki (era)|Reiki]]. * [[:en:Kennin|Kennin]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1203|1203]] [[:en:October 7|October 7]]) – In the incident known as the "Hikii Nōin no Hen" (比企能員の変), the anti-shogunate plot led by the relative of [[Minamoto no Yoriie]] (外戚・比企能員) against [[:en:Hōjō Tokimasa|Hojo Tokimasa]] was uncovered, and the conspirators were executed. * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1863]] [[:en:October 14|October 14]]) – The "Idogataya Incident" (井土ヶ谷事件) occurred. * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1871]] [[:en:October 14|October 14]]) – The government reformed official salaries, switching from an annual salary system to a monthly payment system.
== Births == * [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] 18th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1641|1641]] [[:en:October 5|October 5]]) – [[:en:Kira Yoshinaka|Kira Yoshihisa]], lord of the Tokugawa high family (died [[1702]]). * [[Kansei]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1791]] [[:en:September 29|September 29]]) – {{ill|Sanada Yukinori|ja|真田幸貫|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sanada Yukinori|qq=}}, the 8th lord of the Matsushiro Domain (died [[1852]]). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 11th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1828]] [[:en:October 10|October 10]]) – [[:en:Matsudaira Yoshinaga|Matsudaira Harugaku]], lord of the late Edo-period Echizen Domain and a government minister (died [[1890]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 12nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1841]] [[:en:October 16|October 16]]) – [[:en:Itō Hirobumi|Itō Hirobumi]], a statesman who served as Prime Minister of Japan in the 1st, 5th, 7th, and 10th administrations (died [[1909]]). * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1871]] [[:en:October 15|October 15]]) – [[:en:Takano Iwasaburo|Kōya Iwasaburō]], a social statistician and social activist (died [[1949]]).
== Deaths == * [[Emperor Kaika]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:158 BC|158 BC]] [[:en:October 14|October 14]]) – [[:en:Emperor Kōgen|Emperor Kōgen]], the 8th Emperor of Japan. * [[Karoku]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1227|1227]] [[:en:October 13|October 13]]) – {{ill|Horikawa Tōkugu|ja|堀川通具|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Horikawa Tōkugu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 源通具}}, a waka poet (born [[:en:1171|1171]]). == Commemorations == {{Empty section|date=2021|qq=}}
